                  They all ſaid, Let him be Crucified.
                  V. 22. Inſtead of Accuſing him of any Fault, as he did ſo. or ſo; they were made Judges, which was very abſurd; What ſhall I do unto him? They ſnatch'd him from his place; becauſe they were made Judges;

and this was, either, becauſe he was Blind, and did not underſtand, or becauſe he was afraid.
